---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import summary from '../../../proof/bakeoff/mitosis/summary.json';
import matrix from '../../../benchmarks/bakeoff/mitosis/matrix.json';
const components = Object.keys(summary.generated);
const frameworks = ['react','vue','svelte','solid'];
const ext = {react:'tsx',solid:'tsx',svelte:'svelte',vue:'vue'};
const rows = matrix.rows;
---
<Layout title="Mitosis pilot evidence · Kumo">
<header><p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Candidates</a> / Mitosis</p><h1>Mitosis: pilot evidence</h1><p>Mitosis 0.13.2 generated all 28 component/framework targets. Only Button received real client builds and Chromium interaction, so this is a bounded pilot—not full parity proof.</p></header>
<aside><strong>Diagnosis: candidate API misuse, not an upstream bug.</strong> Generator functions require <code>TranspilerArgs {`{ component, path }`}</code>. The original candidate passed a bare model, making <code>component</code> undefined. Correcting that invocation required no upgrade.</aside>
<section class="stats"><article><strong>28/28</strong><span>sources generated</span></article><article><strong>4/4</strong><span>Button targets passed</span></article><article><strong>76</strong><span>gates passed</span></article><article><strong>372</strong><span>gates not-run</span></article></section>
<section><h2>Target status</h2><p><b>4 passed / 24 partial</b>, with zero failed and zero blocked. “Partial” means generated provenance exists; it does not mean a client or browser pass.</p><div class="table"><table><thead><tr><th>Component</th>{frameworks.map(f=><th>{f}</th>)}</tr></thead><tbody>{components.map(c=><tr><th>{c}</th>{frameworks.map(f=><td class={c==='Button'?'passed':'partial'}>{c==='Button'?'passed':'partial'}<a href={`/benchmarks/bakeoff/mitosis/generated/${f}/${c}.${ext[f]}`}>source</a></td>)}</tr>)}</tbody></table></div></section>
<section><h2>What Button proves</h2><p>React, Vue, Svelte, and Solid each completed a real target client build and Chromium interaction. Their receipts record generated source, build, runtime, console, DOM/ARIA, behavior, and provenance as passed.</p><details><summary>Button gate detail by framework</summary><div class="table"><table><thead><tr><th>Framework</th><th>Passed</th><th>Not-run</th></tr></thead><tbody>{rows.filter(r=>r.component==='Button').map(r=><tr><th>{r.framework}</th><td>{Object.values(r.evidence).filter(v=>v==='passed').length}</td><td>{Object.values(r.evidence).filter(v=>v==='not-run').length}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table></div></details></section>
<section><h2>Adaptation ledger</h2><div class="table"><table><thead><tr><th>Kind</th><th>Change</th><th>Maintenance</th><th>Sensitivity</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>generator</td><td><code>generate({`{ component, path }`})</code> adapter in <code>candidates/mitosis/scripts/generate.mjs</code></td><td>low</td><td>generator API</td></tr></tbody></table></div></section>
<section class="limit"><h2>Strong limitation</h2><p>The other 24 targets were not built or browser-tested. This pilot provides <strong>no SSR, hydration, node-preservation, type, package/tree-shaking, portal, focus-management, asset, or style proof</strong>. Those categories remain not-run; generated source alone cannot answer them.</p></section>
<nav><a href="/bakeoff/" class="touch-link">Compare all architecture candidates →</a></nav>
</Layout>
<style>header{max-width:850px;padding:32px 0 12px}h1{font-size:clamp(38px,5vw,58px);margin:8px 0;letter-spacing:-.04em}header>p:last-child,section>p{color:#475569;line-height:1.65}.eyebrow{font-size:12px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.08em}aside,.limit{margin:24px 0;padding:18px 20px;border-left:4px solid #d97706;background:#fffbeb;line-height:1.6}.stats{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:10px;margin:34px 0}.stats article{padding:18px;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:9px;background:white}.stats strong{display:block;font-size:28px}.stats span{color:#64748b;font-size:12px}section{margin:38px 0}.table{overflow:auto;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:9px}table{width:100%;min-width:650px;border-collapse:collapse;background:white}th,td{padding:11px;border-bottom:1px solid #e5e7eb;text-align:left;font-size:13px}td a{display:block;margin-top:4px;font-size:11px}.passed{color:#166534}.partial{color:#92400e}details{margin-top:14px}summary{cursor:pointer;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:12px}nav{margin:36px 0}@media(max-width:650px){.stats{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}}</style>